DEBT CHAIN NARRATIVE
Trace how a specific causal obligation (secret, threat, promise, betrayal) accumulates
across episodes through new complications and partial collisions, then finally detonates.
Write as a continuous prose narrative of cause → consequence → new cause.
Do not list episodes mechanically — tell the story of the debt.

PINCH POINT DETECTION
A pinch point is the episode-scene where accumulated causal debt collides with a reversal
event, forcing the story into a new trajectory.

  First pinch:  falls somewhere between episodes 7–15
                (the moment the protagonist's initial strategy collapses)
  Second pinch: falls somewhere between episodes 20–30
                (the moment before the final confrontation — all masks off)

To locate a pinch: find the scene where the longest unresolved_debt chain from prior
episodes finally triggers a concrete, irreversible consequence.  Specify the scene_id.

POST-FIRST-PINCH COMMERCIAL FLOW
After the first pinch, classify the story's energy pattern:
  Type A — "Immediate explosion": the reversal detonates at once; pace accelerates;
            audience hook is visceral shock and rapid payoff.
  Type B — "Undercurrent burn": consequences ripple slowly; surface calm hides
            deepening doom; audience hook is dread and dramatic irony.

MARKETING CLIP RECOMMENDATIONS
Recommend exactly 10 clips drawn from specific scenes in the conflict chain.
Distribute them across three structural zones defined by the pinch points you identified above:

  Zone 1 — pre_first_pinch  (ep01 up to but NOT including first_pinch.target_scene_id)
            Target: 4 clips.  These are the hook clips that make a viewer start watching.
            Pick scenes that carry the highest unresolved_debt and clearest character desire.

  Zone 2 — mid              (from first_pinch.target_scene_id up to but NOT including
                              second_pinch.target_scene_id)
            Target: 3 clips.  These cover the escalation arc between the two reversals.

  Zone 3 — post_second_pinch (from second_pinch.target_scene_id to the final episode)
            Target: 3 clips.  These tease the resolution without spoiling it.

FALLBACK RULE (apply only when zone_1 is too shallow):
  If Zone 1 contains fewer than 4 distinct scene_ids in the conflict chain, use every
  available Zone 1 scene (may be 1–3 clips) and compensate by adding the shortfall to
  Zone 2 so the total always reaches 10.  Zone 3 stays fixed at 3.
  Record the actual zone counts in the clip_distribution_note field.

Mix-strategy diversity requirement (across all 10 clips):
  Include at least 2 cold_open, 2 confrontation_cut, 1 montage, and 1 single_scene.
  Distribute strategy types across all three zones — do not cluster all cold_opens in Zone 1.

